shared_text:
Graham HS Art Dept.
September 4 at 7:57 PM ¬∑

Wow! It‚Äôs been a busy week but it is so good to be back!

Our students -in person and remote- have handled new expectations and procedures with grace. (Maybe we adults could take a lesson!)

In Art 1 we are drawing shoes in contour line. Our advanced students in Art 2, 3, and 4 are composing still life drawings with various media. We aren‚Äôt wasting any time.

So, pizza boxes might be a permanent thing now! They make for excellent and sturdy storage portfolios on the go.

Thanks for a fantastic first week back GHS!

Crestview Elementary School - Graham, Texas
August 26 at 1:19 AM ¬∑

We are excited to see you at Meet the Teacher Individual Meetings this Wednesday and Thursday.
Please observe the following guidelines for your meeting:

1. Do not come to campus if you are experiencing COVID-19 symptoms.

2. Only people who have signed up for a meeting time will be able to meet their teacher. If you have not signed up for a meeting time, please register in ParentSqaure OR call the office.

3. Be on time but not more than 5 minutes early for your conference. Remember your teacher will meet you at your assigned door; see the picture attached to this post.

4. The student can be accompanied by 2 parents/guardians.

5. All adults must wear a mask or face shield.

6. Bring your student's school supplies to drop off in their classroom.

The meeting time will last 10 minutes. We must stay on schedule so that all students/families are able to meet their teachers. After the meeting, all new students to campus will be offered a tour. Online registration must be completed prior to your meeting; if you need a login and password please call 940 549 6023.

We will be publishing what we hope is a fun assignment to keep you engaged May 14-22! We will have a GHS Real Life Hacks Challenge for prizes. This challenge will be posted in your Class of Classroom (Class of 2020, Class of 2021,...) today.

CLASSROOM ASSIGNMENT:
Please choose any THREE of the challenges from the GHS Real Life Hack choice board to complete. Attach ONE picture of you participating in each of the THREE challenges. You may complete more than three challenges. As you complete tasks, you will be entered into a drawing for prizes as listed below:
3 tasks verified = 1 ticket in drawing5 tasks verified = 2 tickets in drawing
7 tasks verified = 3 tickets in drawing
We have gift cards and gift certificates for prizes. Prizes come from Sonic, Taco Casa, Chicken Express, Chamber Bucks (Redeemable at most local merchants), United & WalMart. Make sure you engage to win prizes! Prizes will be awarded during laptop return on May 26 & 27!

Celebrating our Seniors! We will be doing daily Senior spotlights to recognize our Seniors. Support your Senior - They are the group most affected by school closures and remote learning as they are missing the spring semester of their senior year.

Graham High Senior Spotlight: Yanelli Miranda

Activities @ GHS: Lady Blues Soccer, Student Council, Key Club, Art Club!

Favorite GHS Memory: My favorite memory of my time @GHS was any time we came together as a school and community to celebrate those around us.

Best advice for future GHS Students: My best advice for students coming through GHS is to remember that going into high school things will change and it might get a bit hard, but KEEP GOING! It's only 4 years and I promise it is all worth it in the end.

GISD Staff Shout Out? I would like to give a shoutout to Mrs. Morris, she is not necessarily a teacher, but she was the best counselor throughout my 4 years of high school.

What are your plans after graduation: I plan to attend The University of North Texas in Denton and study psychology.

What a wonderful celebration of our Senior scholarship recipients last night. I thoroughly enjoyed the 34th Annual Scholarship Awards Ceremony where over $100,000 was given in scholarships to our graduating seniors. I hope all of our students are grateful to have matriculated in a community that supports their dreams!

Look for graduation news today at 9:00 as Mr. Cruse joins Mrs. Krisa De La Cruz on the Graham Chamber of Commerce Facebook page for a live broadcast.
Make sure you are keeping current on Remote Learning assignments. You can do this!

I thoroughly enjoyed the 34th Annual Scholarship Awards Ceremony where over $100,000 was given in scholarships to our graduating seniors. I hope all of our students are grateful to have matriculated in a community that supports their dreams!

Look for graduation news today at 9:00 as Mr. Cruse joins Mrs. Krisa De La Cruz on the Graham Chamber of Commerce Facebook page for a live broadcast.
Make sure you are keeping current on Remote Learning assignments. You can do this!

Good Morning with Gordy Episode 25

Tonight marks the 34th year for the Graham High School Scholarship Awards Ceremony. We are grateful to all of the benefactors who support Graham High School graduates!

Thank you for joining us for the evening!

Thank you to Mrs. Brandi Menard for her diligence and effort in putting this presentation together!

Graham High School
April 21 at 2:00 PM ¬∑

GHS has opened up the online forms that all athletes, marching band and cheerleaders will need to compete to participate next year. It would be great to go ahead and get the Rank One forms completed now as opposed to having to complete during the summer. All forms must be completed prior to student participation in GHS events in the summer/fall @ GHS. You will need your student's student ID number. This number can be found on the Student Information tab of Skyward Family Access listed under "other ID."

UIL has not yet decided if new physicals are required for the upcoming year. We will let everyone know once something official happens on that front.

Here is the link that the parents would need to go to complete the online forms

https://grahamisd.rankonesport.com/New/NewInstructionsPage.aspx

The parents would also need their student's ID number to complete the forms.

Online Forms

Online Forms

See more at
grahamisd.rankonesport.com

Celebrating our Seniors! We will be doing daily Senior spotlights to recognize our Seniors. Support your Senior - They are the group most affected by school closures and remote learning as they are missing the spring semester of their senior year.

Graham High Senior Spotlight: Kat Slavings

Activities @ GHS: FFA, Livestock showing.

Favorite GHS Memory: Greenhand camp for FFA

Best advice for future GHS Students: Don't listen to the rumors made about you, you know the truth. Thats all that matters.

GISD Staff Shout Out? Mr. Lange

What are your plans after graduation: Air Force Mechanic

Celebrating our Seniors! We will be doing daily Senior spotlights to recognize our Seniors. Support your Senior - They are the group most affected by school closures and remote learning as they are missing the spring semester of their senior year.

Graham High Senior Spotlight: Evan Ranger

Activities @ GHS: Basketball & Golf

Favorite GHS Memory: Basketball season/ every year was a grind! But my favorite memory was making it to the regional tournament my Junior year/ Being around all the boys the grade above me my junior year.

Best advice for future GHS Students:Self improvement/ be the best person you can and work on your craft everyday.

GISD Staff Shout Out? Coach Morris- for always being there and being 100% real with me all the time. and helping me for life after High-school/ Custodian- Mrs. Manriquez - the nicest person I've ever met; she made me become a better person.

What are your plans after graduation: Planning to further basketball career at Brookhaven Jr College.

Celebrating our Seniors! We will be doing daily Senior spotlights to recognize our Seniors. Support your Senior - They are the group most affected by school closures and remote learning as they are missing the spring semester of their senior year.

Graham High Senior Spotlight: Evan Ranger

Activities @ GHS: Basketball & Golf

Favorite GHS Memory: Basketball season/ every year was a grind! But my favorite memory was making it to the regional tournament my Junior year/ Being around all the boys the grade above me my junior year.

Best advice for future GHS Students:Self improvement/ be the best person you can and work on your craft everyday.

GISD Staff Shout Out? Coach Morris- for always being there and being 100% real with me all the time. and helping me for life after High-school/ Custodian- Mrs. Manriquez - the nicest person I've ever met; she made me become a better person.

What are your plans after graduation: Planning to further basketball career at Brookhaven Jr College.

post_text: Honoring the Class of 2020- During the past several weeks, Mr. Gordy and I have been discussing various creative ways we may be able to honor members of the Class of 2020 in addition to the senior spotlights that are being posted via our social media. Yesterday, GHS counselor, Mrs. Morris, Mr. Gordy, and I met to begin working on a plan to formally announce and highlight our Honor Graduates. As we move forward with know parameters, we will develop a plan, have it approved by local authorities. Following this, we will meet online with the senior class officers, senior members of the GHS SALT team, and senior members of the YouthLead team to seek student input. After the plan is fully developed, Mr. Gordy and I will meet online with the entire GHS Class of 2020.

post_text: Governor Abbott Press Conference- At Noon today the Governor issued several orders to begin the process of reopening the Texas economy. In regards to schools, he issued an order that deems it unsafe to resume having school in our school buildings. Additionally, he stated the Commissioner of Education, Mike Morath, will be providing schools with guidelines regarding ceremonies such as graduation.

What are your plans after graduation: I plan on staying here in graham to finish my basics here at NCTC before transferring over to UNT to major in interior design

Favorite GHS Memory: Going on a culinary trip with my friends and trying a ton of different foods.

Celebrating our Seniors! We will be doing daily Senior spotlights to recognize our Seniors. Support your Senior - They are the group most affected by school closures and remote learning as they are missing the spring semester of their senior year.

Graham High Senior Spotlight: Natalie Minyard

Natalie has been involved in Bella Blues, choir, and the Student Activity Leadership Team at Graham high School. Her favorite memories at Graham High School are Friday night football games with the Bellas & band.

Natalie's advice to younger students is to not be afraid to go to any teacher for help, they are there for you, to help you. May it be home related or school related.

I want to shout out not just one teacher but all my teachers, they have helped me so much with my time here at GISD that I could not thank them enough. They have gone out of their way to help me when I struggled with my health.

Natalie plans to continue her passion for dance at TJC and go for a dance minor followed by a psychology degree.

Graham HS Art Dept.
March 30 at 4:48 PM ¬∑

Today is our first day of online learning! Whether you are a parent or a student, please do not let this stress you out. We are all learning together and we will get the hang of this!

Encourage your student to check his or her email. I have a Google Classroom set up, where I will post our weekly assignments. You will also be able to see assignment information via the GHS Assignment calendar, although my private Classrooms will have more detailed information. My "office hours" specifically for email questions or chatting are 8:30 - 10:30, and we will have daily "hangouts" via Google Meet from 1:30-3:30, when your student can drop in to say hi or ask questions. This video conference link is only available to students in my Google Classroom.

This is an unprecedented time in all our lives - I hope that you are journaling, videoing, doodling, and making art to remember what it's been like. Your kids will ask!

Graham HS Art Dept.
February 22 at 11:59 PM ¬∑

üé® Today 22 GHS artists traveled to Wichita Falls with a combined 28 original artworks to compete at the Regional VASE contest. Lots of time, thought, hard work, and energy went into this endeavor; I'm very proud we had so many brave competitors. We had *fierce* competition in the region this year.

üèÜ I'm thrilled to say that 20 of their pieces medaled at the event - meaning their artwork and interviews scored the highest possible rating of "4". Additionally, sophomore McKynna Bozeman's 3D artwork was selected to advance to the State contest in April! A well-deserved honor!

üíñ Congratulations to all of our competitors today! Our students represented Graham well - they were respectful and composed. Leave them lots of love for competing in this event!
